http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/CPIM-worker-friend-injured-in-bomb-attack/article13980149.ece

A Communist Party of India (Marxist) [CPI(M)] worker and his friend were injured in a bomb attack by alleged Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh (RSS) workers near Chakkarakkal here on Sunday.The CPI(M) worker, identified as Sanesh (25), suffered serious injuries in his leg in the attack, while his friend, identified as Rajesh (25), suffered minor injuries in his arm. The former has been admitted to a hospital in Kozhikode.The police said the duo were riding on a motorcycle when the attack occurred at around 5.30 p.m. on the Pallipoyil road under the Chakkarakkal police station limits. The attack was carried out by a six-member gang who reached the spot on four motorcycles. One of the legs of Sanesh was nearly severed in the attack as a bomb hurled by the assailants hit the leg and exploded.He was first rushed to the AKG Hospital here and from there to the hospital in Kozhikode. Rajesh was admitted in a local hospital.The police said that all the six attackers have been identified. After the attack they hurled several bombs to scare the people and to escape after abandoning their two-wheelers. Chakkarakkal and nearby areas had recently witnessed tension following clashes between the CPI(M) and RSS workers.The attack occurred a day after CPI(M) Polit Bureau member Pinarayi Vijayan accepted RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat's offer of talks to end political violence in Kannur. The CPI(M) leader said on Saturday that the party was ready to talk to the RSS. He had alleged that the RSS was instigating violence in the district with the knowledge of its leadership.The attack was carried out by a six-member gang who reached the spot on motorbikes.